DataElement.preferredName: Tissue Source Study Site and Disease TCGA Code
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Code that represents the institution source and study disease related to the tumor tissue submitted for The Cancer Genome Atlas project.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Tissue Source Site And Disease Identification
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A tissue sample, or entire tumor that is removed for microscopic examination._Where something is available or from where it originates._A facilty in which study/protocol activities are conducted._An article which expresses the relation of connection or addition. It is used to conjoin a word with a word, a clause with a clause, or a sentence with a sentence._Any abnormal condition of the body or mind that causes discomfort, dysfunction, or distress to the person affected or those in contact with the person. ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A tissue sample, or entire tumor that is removed for microscopic examination.

Concepts.definition: Tissue sample that contains an abnormal cellular infiltrate forming a solid mass. The abnormal cellular component can be benign or malignant. Tumor samples are obtained for microscopic examination and/or molecular analysis.

Concepts.definition: Where something is available or from where it originates.
A facility in which study/protocol activities are conducted.
An article which expresses the relation of connection or addition. It is used to conjoin a word with a word, a clause with a clause, or a sentence with a sentence.

Any abnormal condition of the body or mind that causes discomfort, dysfunction, or distress to the person affected or those in contact with the person. The term is often used broadly to include injuries, disabilities, syndromes, symptoms, deviant behaviors, and atypical variations of structure and function.
The procedure of having an identity established.
